{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.8",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 8,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 8",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 8 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:1",
      "text": "Then Bildad the Shuhite answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:2",
      "text": "“ How long will you speak these things? Shall the words of your mouth be a mighty wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:3",
      "text": "Does God pervert justice? Or does the Almighty pervert righteousness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:4",
      "text": "If your children have sinned against him, he has delivered them into the hand of their disobedience.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:5",
      "text": "If you want to seek God diligently, make your supplication to the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:6",
      "text": "If you were pure and upright, surely now he would awaken for you, and make the habitation of your righteousness prosperous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:7",
      "text": "Though your beginning was small, yet your latter end would greatly increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:8",
      "text": "“ Please inquire of past generations. Find out about the learning of their fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:9",
      "text": "(For we are but of yesterday, and know nothing, because our days on earth are a shadow.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:10",
      "text": "Shall they not teach you, tell you, and utter words out of their heart?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:11",
      "text": "“ Can the papyrus grow up without mire? Can the rushes grow without water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:12",
      "text": "While it is yet in its greenness, not cut down, it withers before any other reed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:13",
      "text": "So are the paths of all who forget God. The hope of the godless man will perish,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:14",
      "text": "whose confidence will break apart, whose trust is a spider’s web.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:15",
      "text": "He will lean on his house, but it will not stand. He will cling to it, but it will not endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:16",
      "text": "He is green before the sun. His shoots go out along his garden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:17",
      "text": "His roots are wrapped around the rock pile. He sees the place of stones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:18",
      "text": "If he is destroyed from his place, then it will deny him, saying, ‘ I have not seen you.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:19",
      "text": "Behold, this is the joy of his way. Out of the earth, others will spring.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:20",
      "text": "“ Behold, God will not cast away a blameless man, neither will he uphold the evildoers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:21",
      "text": "He will still fill your mouth with laughter, your lips with shouting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.8.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:22",
      "text": "Those who hate you will be clothed with shame. The tent of the wicked will be no more.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
